solution: class Solution {
    public boolean checkSubarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put(0, -1);
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            sum += nums[i];
            int rem = k == 0 ? sum : sum % k;
            if (map.containsKey(rem)) {
                if (i - map.get(rem) > 1) return true;
            } else {
                map.put(rem, i);
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(min(n, k))
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses prefix-sum remainder tracking with a hash map to detect subarrays whose sum is a multiple of k in one pass. The key insight is that if two prefix sums have the same remainder mod k, the subarray between them has sum divisible by k.

